however, that its policy was not to build up significant long-term loans.
The group has raised Pounds 196m over the last two years.
IMS, which manufactures specialised injectable delivery systems, had
turnover of Dollars 39m last year but only broke even before interest costs.
Medeva said it expected the net effect of IMS not to be significant in 1992
but that it would make a net contribution from 1993.
