evidently doesn't now. 'Who was the first socialist?' he asked recently,
before answering his own question: 'Christopher Columbus, because he didn't
know where he was going and when he got there he didn't know where he was,
but he didn't care because he didn't have to pay for it.'
A listening Thai economist commented later that he'd heard the crack before.
But then the question had been: 'Who was the first economist?'
