<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUN 92 / World News In Brief: Wimbledon
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Jeremy Bates held match point against ninth seed Guy Forget of France, but
failed to become the first British player since Roger Taylor in 1973 to
reach the quarter-finals of the men's singles, losing 7-6 4-6 6-3 6-7 3-6.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
