<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUN 92 / Britain ready on VAT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN is ready to allow the Community to legislate on value added tax
rates, provided its whisky exports are not penalised by higher excise
duties.
This was signalled last night by Mr Norman Lamont, the chancellor, during
complex but ultimately unsuccessful EC bargaining in Luxembourg intended to
align indirect consumer goods tax rates.
