<TEXT>
DOW CORNING, the 50-50 joint venture between Dow Chemical and Corning, the
glassware company, hopes to sell most of the assets of its medical devices
business, except for assets related to its discontinued production of
silicone breast implants, by the end of the year.
Dow Corning expects its revenues - which come mainly from the manufacture of
