over safety earlier this year, was discontinued in January during a review
by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA). Dow Corning withdrew completely
from the breast implant business in March.
Dow Corning said the decision to sell its medical devices business was 'part
of our ongoing strategic review.' The company said it primary expertise had
come from materials innovation rather than fabrication and distribution.
Last year, Dow Corning made a net profit of Dollars 152.9m on turnover of
Dollars 1.8bn.
