FT  30 JUN 92 / Aircraft staff start work-to-rule
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ABOUT 400 aircraft maintenance staff at Dan Air Engineering have started a
work-to-rule and partial overtime ban to force FLS Aerospace, the Danish
owner of the company, to improve a 6 per cent pay offer. They expect flights
from Manchester, Stansted and Gatwick airports to be disrupted.
