Angeles to Phoenix, Arizona, 370 miles away. A second quake - measuring 7.0
 -rumbled through the area three hours later, cracking roads.
The quakes were bigger than the tremor that hit the San Francisco area in
1989, killing 70 people and causing billions of dollars in damage.
