<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 92 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The French franc firmed at the end of last week to its best levels against
the D-Mark in almost a month as political tensions surrounding European
monetary union faded. The franc ended at 2 per cent of its allowed swing
above its central Ecu rate.  The peseta was undermined by news that the
Spanish budget deficit rose to Ptas 1.1 trillion in the first five months of
1992 against Ptas 700bn in the same period last year.
