<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 92 / World News in Brief: Bad loans hit societies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Building societies' total bad debt provisions are expected to reach 1.17bn
this year, says a report from UBS Phillips &amp; Drew. But while bad debts make
up about 0.7 per cent of the loans of the top 20 societies, they form 2.78
per cent of lending by big clearing banks.
