stockmarket commission suspended trading in Progreso following the
announcement of the bid.
The acquisition and the subsequent merger have been prompted by the
breakdown of negotiations to sell Progreso to La Caixa, the Barcelona-based
savings bank that ranks as Spain's biggest financial institution. La Caixa
is understood to have objected to the concentration of Progreso's loans and
to the Pta18bn to Pta20bn price placed on bank.
