FT  27 JUN 92 / Finance &amp; The Family (At a glance): Low-cost share service
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Allied-Lyons is launching a low-cost share dealing service with commissions
of just 1 per cent on its own shares and no minimum. Purchases can be made
on a lump sum basis or via monthly savings of Pounds 50 or more. The company
is also launching two personal equity plans - a corporate Pep, with an
annual Pounds 6,000 limit, and a single company Pep, with a ceiling of
Pounds 3,000. There will be an initial fee of Pounds 10 plus VAT and an
annual management charge of 0.5 per cent, plus VAT. Brokerage fees within
the Pep will be 0.25 per cent, plus stamp duty. The Pep is being
administered by Bradford &amp; Bingley (0274-555677) and details of the share
dealing service can be obtained on 071-606-1768.
