<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Improved Pounds 2.87m from Syltone
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Syltone, the maker of specialist ancillary equipment for the transportation
industry, lifted pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.73m to Pounds 2.87m in the
year to March 31. Turnover advanced from Pounds 33.7m to Pounds 34.9m.
Mr Tony Clegg, the chairman, said the result had been achieved despite a
serious setback at Rotocold, the vehicle refrigeration and air conditioning
subsidiary. Looking ahead, he said the company would continue to explore new
opportunities and markets.
A final dividend of 6.3p (6p) is proposed for a total of 9.45p (9p), payable
from earnings of 22.22p (22.18p) per share.
</TEXT>
