FT  27 JUN 92 / City cleans up after IRA bomb
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE IRA claimed responsibility yesterday for the latest bomb attack in
London's financial centre, Bethan Hutton writes.
The bomb - left under a car in Coleman Street, near the Guildhall, on
Thursday evening - caused minimal disruption to businesses in the City
yesterday. No one was injured in the blast, but the bomb left a crater in
the street, and glass was shattered in surrounding buildings.
At Slaughter and May, the solicitors whose offices were worst hit, work was
continuing as usual. The company - which had already taken precautions
against terrorist attack - said damage was restricted to glass in two
meeting rooms and five offices, and a clean-up would make them usable by
Monday.
